#v(0.5em)

Jakarta City produces 6,270 tons of waste daily, with 21% missing from formal management channels and ending up as illegal dumping in riverbanks, vacant land, and densely populated areas. The lack of easy and transparent reporting mechanisms results in low citizen participation and slow government response. This proposal aims to develop a City Illegal Dumping Reporting and Management System based on mobile technology and Geographic Information System (GIS). The system integrates automatic geolocation reporting, real-time status tracking, government analytics dashboard, point-based gamification with rewards, and temporary disposal site directory. The development methodology uses Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) with Agile Scrum approach over 6 months. Expected outcomes include 15,000 valid reports per year with 85% resolution rate within 7 days and user satisfaction score of 4.2/5.0. The required budget of Rp751,000,000 covers software development, cloud infrastructure, socialization, and gamification incentives. This system offers novelty in comprehensive gamification integration, GIS-based predictive analytics, and transparent citizen-government loop.

